							<div id="EyreSquare">					
							<h4 class="desch4">Eyre Square Shopping Centre</h4>
							<p>Located in the heart of Galway has been described as Irelands most modern and yet historic shopping centre. 
							The centre is Galway City's liveliest and attractive meeting place incorporating over 60 national and international 
							shopping outlets.						
							<a href="http://www.eyresquarecentre.com/"><br /> more...</a></p>
							</div>
							
							<div id="Restaurants">					
							<h4 class="desch4">Restaurants and Traditional Irish Music Pubs</h4>
							<p>Pubs in ireland were traditionally not the place to go for a full meal but now compete with restaurants for the quality 
							of their food.
							The standard and type of pub food varies enormously but here is a small guide to some of the best.						
							<a href="http://www.galwaycitypubguide.com/pub-food.html"><br /> more...</a></p>
							</div>
							
							<div id="Beaches">					
							<h4 class="desch4">Sandy Beaches</h4>
							<p>The beach at Salthill is located in Galway city and overlooking Galway Bay. The beach is lifeguarded from mid-May 
							to the end of September from 11 am to 7 pm. Salthill beach has been a blue flag beach and enormously popular in fine
							weather during the summer.						
							<a href="http://www.galwaytourism.ie/ptop-5-beaches.html"><br /> more...</a></p>
							</div>
							
							<div id="CoastalWalks">					
							<h4 class="desch4">Spectacular Coastal Walks</h4>
							<p>There are many highly recommended walks, for instance the Ardmore Cliff Walk (5km, 60 mins), Cunnigar - a long
							sandy strip across the mouth of Dungarvan Bay(6km, 90 mins), and Lady Louisa’s Walk from Lismore Castle (2 km, 30 mins)						
							<br /> <a href="http://www.ireland.com/en-gb/what-is-available/walking-and-hiking/destinations/republic-of-ireland/galway/"> more...</a></p>
							</div>							
							
						</div>
					
						<div id="descRight">
						
							<div id="Tour">					
							<h4 class="desch4">Bust tour of Galway</h4>
							<p>The original Galway City Tour is a hop-on hop-off tour that allows you to see the very best 
							of the City of the Tribes. The majority of popular sights in Galway are located near the city centre. 
							This tour gives an overview of Galway and tells the story from how it once was, to how it became what it is today.						
							<a href="http://lallytours.com/blog/travel/galway-city-tour/"><br /> more...</a></p>
							</div>
							
							<div id="Connemara">					
							<h4 class="desch4">Connemara</h4>
							<p>Connemara, situated at the very edge of Europe, on the west coast of Ireland, is one of the most beautiful, 
							unspoilt places it's possible to find.						
							<a href="http://www.connemara.ie/en/"><br /> more...</a></p>
							</div>
							
							<div id="CliffsOfMoher">					
							<h4 class="desch4">Cliffs of Moher</h4>
							<p>The Cliffs of Moher are an incredible sight that will remain with you long after you’ve left…						
							<a href="http://www.ireland.com/en-us/articles/cliffs-of-moher/"><br /> more...</a></p>
							</div>
							
							<div id="TheAranIslands">					
							<h4 class="desch4">The Aran Islands</h4>
							<p>The Aran Islands are located just off Galway and Doolin. A true Irish experience awaits, locals speak 
							Irish as well as English in a setting of Celtic churches of historical significance including World Heritage 
							site Dun Aonghasa which is set on dramatic 300 ft cliff edge.						
							<a href="http://www.aranislands.ie/"><br /> more...</a></p>
							</div>
						
						</div>
									
		                <div id="Facilities">					
							<h4 class="desch4">Other Facilities</h4>
							<p>There are many opportunities for entertainment in Galway. To name a few, horseriding takes in the beaches, back-country 
							trails and mountains on short rides and treks. Ellen's B&amp;B is also well placed for golfing holidays in Ireland. 
							You can choose from various water sports and there is rock fishing at Ardmore Head where wrasse, conger, pollock, codling, 
							coalfish and mackerel are all common. 
							Please ask reception for complimentary fishing equipment. Bikes are available for hire.  </p>
							<p>Sightseeing tours can be arranged at the B&amp;B at a discount for: Connemara, Cliffs of Moher, 
							The Aran Islands and a bus tour of Galway City. All tickets can be purchased on arrival. </p>
							<p>The nearest bus stop is only 60 yards away. <a href="http://www.galwaytransport.info/2009/07/city-bus-services.html">
							Bus Services</a>
							<br />Taxis are available on request. <a href="http://www.galwaytaxis.com/">Taxi Service</a></p>
